Modern browsers such as Firefox 2 can show directly in the URL-field, which rss-feeds are provided by a page. This is facilitated by some descriptive text in the <head>-section of the page.
Confluence should be able to pick up all rss-feeds from a page and generate the required descriptive section for the generated html, such that browser can show links to all rss-feeds directly in the URL.

