under the operations area on the "info" page there should be a pipe that separates the "Copy" operation from the "Email" operation. The pipe is not there and this could be confusing for users.

See attached image for more detail.

LDAP groups sometimes could not be retrieved for a user. This leads to incorrect privileges. 

This happens because of incorrect serialization/de-serialization of cached ldap user object.
in DefaultLDAPUser class we declare a _distinguishedName_ field as transient. 
{noformat}
private transient String distinguishedName;
{noformat}

When this object is serialization/de-serialization (which is happens in clustered cache) this filed will be null but we still use it to construct ldap query. See this support [case|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CSP-10204].

We need to figure out if there is a reason why we declare this field as transient and if there is no good reason make it non-transient.

See a demonstration here:  http://extranet.atlassian.com/display/~jnolen/PageName

However, the gist is that is an anchor name is too long, the link doesn't render correctly. For example:

{noformat}
[blah|PageName#PageName-AnchorWhichIsVeryLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLongLong]
{noformat}

results in a link that looks like:

{noformat}
http://extranet.atlassian.com/display/~jnolen/PageName#PageName-ageNameAnchorWhichIsVeryLongLongLongLongLongL...
{noformat}


Also, any anchor name that is too long will get truncated in elipsis, whether or not it's an autogenerated anchor.

